# Slide Deck Creation

## Quick start

1. Copy the `slide-template/` folder to a new folder (e.g. `decks\q2-board-deck\`)
2. Rename the `<title>` tag and the title slide `<h1>` to the new deck name
3. Add, remove, or reorder slides as needed
4. Replace placeholder content with real data
5. After structural changes, renumber all `data-slide` attributes starting from 0
6. Update the localStorage key version (e.g. `v1` → `v2`) if slide positions changed

## Template structure

The template is a single `index.html` file (~1500 lines) with:
- CSS styles (lines 1-770)
- Slide HTML (lines 770-1020)
- JavaScript: editing, nav, sorter, comments, charts, heatmaps, fullscreen, mobile (lines 1040+)

Required asset folders (copy with the template):
- `assets/fonts/` — Roughwell.otf, Generation1970-Light.otf, Generation1970.otf, Generation1970-Bold.otf
- `assets/logos/` — Flow-Logo-FADED-CREAM.svg (used on title slide)

External dependency: `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@4.4.1` (loaded via CDN)

## Slide types reference

Each slide is a `<div class="slide" data-slide="N">` inside `<div class="deck" id="deck">`.

### 0. Title / Cover
```html
<div class="slide slide-title title-a" data-slide="0">
  <h1>Deck Title</h1>
  <p class="date">February 2026</p>
  <div class="accent-bar"></div>
  <img src="assets/logos/Flow-Logo-FADED-CREAM.svg" class="title-logo-corner" alt="Flow" />
</div>
```
Dark midnight background, Roughwell headline, cream text. Always position 0.

### 1. Table of Contents
```html
<div class="slide" data-slide="1">
  <div class="s-header"><div class="pill">Flow</div><div class="s-title">Table of Contents</div></div>
  <div class="s-body">
    <ul class="toc-list" id="tocList"></ul>
  </div>
</div>
```
Auto-populated by `buildTOC()` from section dividers. No manual editing needed.

### 2. Section Divider
```html
<div class="slide slide-divider" data-slide="2">
  <div class="accent-bar"></div>
  <h2>Section Name</h2>
</div>
```
Midnight background. Insert before each major section. TOC auto-detects these.

### 3. Text + Bullets
```html
<div class="slide" data-slide="3">
  <div class="s-header"><div class="pill">Section</div><div class="s-title">Slide Title</div></div>
  <div class="s-body">
    <ul class="bl">
      <li><strong>Point</strong> -- detail</li>
      <li><strong>Point</strong> -- detail
        <ul class="sub"><li>Sub-detail</li></ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
```
Pill badge shows section name. Bullets use en-dash prefix (automatic via CSS).

### 4. KPI / Metric Cards
```html
<div class="slide" data-slide="4">
  <div class="s-header"><div class="pill">Section</div><div class="s-title">Key Metrics</div></div>
  <div class="s-body">
    <div class="exec-grid">
      <div class="exec-card wide">
        <div class="label">Category</div>
        <div class="val-row">
          <div class="item"><span class="lbl">Label</span><span class="v">$24.0M</span></div>
          <div class="item"><span class="lbl">Label</span><span class="v neg">($3.2M)</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="note">Footnote</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exec-card"><div class="label">Metric</div><div class="val">$42.1M</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```
3-column grid. `.wide` spans all 3. `.neg` for red negatives. `.note` for footnotes.

### 5. Chart
```html
<div class="slide" data-slide="5">
  <div class="s-header"><div class="pill">Section</div><div class="s-title">Chart Title</div></div>
  <div class="s-body">
    <div class="chart-area" style="max-height:420px"><canvas id="myChartId"></canvas></div>
  </div>
</div>
```
Then add the chart config in the `drawCharts()` function (see Charts section below).

### 6. Narrow Table
```html
<div class="slide" data-slide="6">
  <div class="s-header"><div class="pill">Section</div><div class="s-title">Table Title</div></div>
  <div class="s-body">
    <table class="ft">
      <thead><tr><th>Category</th><th>FY2026</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Item</td><td>$8.4M</td></tr>
        <tr class="total"><td>Total</td><td>$20.3M</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
```
Use `table.ft` for 2-3 column centered tables. `.total` for bold total rows.

### 7. Wide Table (Heatmap)
```html
<div class="slide" data-slide="7">
  <div class="s-header"><div class="pill">Section</div><div class="s-title">Detail</div></div>
  <div class="s-body">
    <div class="opco-table-wrap">
      <table class="opco heatmap">
        <thead><tr><th></th><th>Col A</th><th>Col B</th><th>Total</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Row</td><td data-v="120">$120K</td><td data-v="85">$85K</td><td>$205K</td></tr>
          <tr class="total-row"><td>Total</td><td>$120K</td><td>$85K</td><td>$205K</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```
Use `table.opco` for many columns. Add `.heatmap` for auto-shading. `data-v` attributes drive intensity. `.total-row` for totals. Wrap in `.opco-table-wrap` for sticky headers + scroll.

### 8. Two-Column
```html
<div class="slide" data-slide="8">
  <div class="s-header"><div class="pill">Section</div><div class="s-title">Title</div></div>
  <div class="s-body">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <div class="col-head">Left</div>
        <ul class="bl"><li>Point</li></ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="col-head">Right</div>
        <ul class="bl"><li>Point</li></ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### 9. Table + Commentary
```html
<div class="slide" data-slide="9">
  <div class="s-header"><div class="pill">Section</div><div class="s-title">Summary</div></div>
  <div class="s-body" style="display:flex; gap:28px; align-items:flex-start;">
    <div class="opco-table-wrap" style="flex:0 0 auto;">
      <table class="opco" style="width:360px;">
        <thead><tr><th></th><th>FY2026</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Item</td><td>$14.2M</td></tr>
          <tr class="total-row"><td>Total</td><td>$17.2M</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="content" style="flex:1; margin-top:10px;">
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>Topic</strong> -- explanation</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Charts

Charts use Chart.js. Each chart needs two things:
1. A `<canvas id="uniqueId">` inside `.chart-area` in the slide HTML
2. A config block in the `drawCharts()` function at the bottom of the file

### Adding a chart

Find `drawCharts()` and add a new block:
```javascript
var el = document.getElementById('myChartId');
if (el) new Chart(el, {
  type: 'bar',       // 'bar', 'line', 'doughnut', etc.
  data: {
    labels: ['A', 'B', 'C'],
    datasets: [{ data: [10, 20, 30], backgroundColor: sun, borderRadius: 4, barThickness: 28 }]
  },
  options: {
    indexAxis: 'y',   // horizontal bars; omit for vertical
    responsive: true, maintainAspectRatio: false,
    plugins: { legend: { display: false }, tooltip: { enabled: false } },
    scales: { x: { display: false, beginAtZero: true }, y: { grid: { display: false } } }
  },
  plugins: [barLabelPlugin]  // reuse the existing plugin for bar labels
});
```

### Waterfall chart pattern (stacked bar)
Two datasets: transparent base (spacer) + colored value. Both with `stacked: true`.
```javascript
datasets: [
  { label: 'Base', data: [0, 80, 60], backgroundColor: 'transparent', borderWidth: 0 },
  { label: 'Value', data: [100, 20, 60], backgroundColor: [olive, ocean, olive] }
]
// scales: { x: { stacked: true }, y: { stacked: true, display: false } }
```

### Flow palette for charts
- Sunlight `#E89700` — positive values, highlights
- Olive `#767317` — totals (beginning/ending bars)
- Ocean `#7DADBB` — primary category
- Roots `#8C4500` — negatives, decreases
- Heart `#F99AA9` — secondary negatives, RE items
- Midnight `#3D3D3D` — neutral bars

## Adding and removing slides

1. Insert or delete the `<div class="slide" ...>...</div>` block
2. Renumber all `data-slide` attributes sequentially starting from 0
3. Make sure the first slide has `class="slide slide-title title-a active"` (the `active` class)
4. The nav counter initial text can be updated but is overwritten by JS on load
5. If the localStorage key still points to old structure, bump the version suffix (e.g. `v1` → `v2`) in the `STORAGE_KEY` variable

## Brand constraints

- Colors: use the Flow palette (Moonlight, Midnight, Sunlight, Heart, Ocean, Olive, Roots). No generic blue.
- Fonts: Roughwell for headlines, Generation 1970 for slide titles, Poppins for body text
- Tone: first-person plural (we, us), no exclamation points, no emojis, Oxford comma
- Negatives always in parentheses: ($3.2M) not -$3.2M
- Numbers in tables use tabular-nums (automatic via CSS)

## Deployment (optional)

- Push folder to GitHub, connect to Vercel for instant hosting
- For PDF export, add a Vercel serverless function using Puppeteer (see `library/decks/f1-deck/` `/api/pdf` for reference)
